Star Wars: Episode IV - A New Hope (1977) 124 min

DESCRIPTION:
A spirited farm boy joins rebel forces to save the galaxy from the evil Empire. (with two audio commentaries; the first is ported from the 2004 DVD release; the second is edited together from various interviews for the 2011 Blu-ray release)

SPECS IN BRIEF:
M4V file for iTunes/iDevices
V: 1280x544 23.98 fps h.264 @ 3000 Kbps
A: 160 Kbps 2.0 AAC &amp; 384 Kbps 5.1 AC-3 / 96 Kbps AAC 2.0 (commentaries)
S: English, English SDH, Spanish, French, Brazilian Portuguese, Portuguese
   English subs for Huttese dialogue burned-in
C: 50 (Named)

SOURCE:
Retail Blu-ray Disc

PLAYBACK:
Encoded &amp; tagged for iTunes and Apple devices (iPad, iPhone 4, etc) that can handle HD video, including *all* versions -- 2007, 2010, 2012 -- of the AppleTV set top box.

